article.description: Hawaii races past UC Riverside in100-69 rout
article.headline: Hawaii races past UC Riverside in100-69 rout
article.linkText: Hawaii races past UC Riverside in100-69 rout
article.story: HONOLULU -- Christian Standhardinger scored 27 points as Hawaii tuned its Big West Conference home opener into a rout, racing past California Riverside 100-69 Saturday night The Rainbow Warriors raced to a 15-1 lead in the opening minutes. Standhardinger and Brandon Spearman each scored 15 first-half points as Hawaii built a 56-30 halftime advantage. Hawaii (12-5, 1-2 Big West) got 18 points from Spearman, 16 from Isaac Fotu and 12 from Garrett Nevels. Hawaii shot 34 of 69 from the field and held a 42-28 advantage on the boards. The Warriors now are 10-2 at home, winning eight of their last nine home games, and snapped a five-game conference losing streak. Sam Finley scored 19 points to lead UC Riverside (5-12, 0-3). Austin Quick added 15 points and Chris Patton 11. The Highlanders were 20 of 51 from the field (39.2 percent) and were just 3 of 17 from 3-point range.
